&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;/collection&gt;
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;==
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; 201 Created
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; Location: http://myserver.com/service/items
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; Content-Type: application/xml
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; ...
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; Remove collection:
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; ==&gt;
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; DELETE /service/items
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;==
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; 200 OK
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; Removing a single item from the collection:
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; ==&gt;
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; DELETE /service/items/item1
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;==
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; 200 OK
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; However, I am finding supporting the other operations a bit tricky
&gt; i.e.
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; what methods can I use to:
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; Add single or multiple items to the collection. (PUT doesn&#39;t seem to
&gt; be
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; right here as per HTTP 1.1 RFC)
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; Remove multiple items from the collection in one transaction. (DELETE
&gt; &gt;&gt; &gt; doesn&#39;t seem to right here either)
